# soul_defaults.sha256 — normalized SHA-256 of every default soul.md ever shipped.
#
# GENERATED by tests/gen_soul_hashes.sh — do not hand-edit. Regenerate after any
# change to rapp_brainstem/soul.md (test_local_agents.py enforces this in CI).
#
# Normalization (rapp_brainstem/soul_hash.py, mirrored natively in install.ps1):
#   strip UTF-8 BOM; CRLF->LF; strip trailing space/tab per line; exactly one
#   trailing newline; then sha256 (lowercase hex).
#
# On upgrade the installers refresh soul.md ONLY if its normalized hash is listed
# here (an unmodified historical default) AND differs from the new default. Any
# other soul — or one that cannot be normalized — is preserved byte-for-byte.
#
# Format: <64-hex normalized sha256>  # <representative commit>
